and reentry licensing regimes

00:30:39.103 --> 00:30:43.074
with a streamlined system
by March 1, 2019,

00:30:43.074 --> 00:30:45.310
to be completed at
that point on or before.

00:30:45.843 --> 00:30:48.079
Recommendation Two directs
the Department of Commerce

00:30:48.079 --> 00:30:51.616
to consolidate all space
commerce responsibilities

00:30:53.218 --> 00:30:54.886
in the Office
of the Secretary,

00:30:56.888 --> 00:30:58.823
as Wilbur described,

00:30:58.823 --> 00:31:02.060
and also develop a system that 
facilitates mission authorization

00:31:02.060 --> 00:31:04.596
for commercial
space activities.

00:31:04.596 --> 00:31:07.865
There are other recommendations
related to that

00:31:07.865 --> 00:31:10.735
that the Secretary
enumerated quite well.

00:31:10.735 --> 00:31:14.505
Recommendation Three directs
the National Telecommunication

00:31:14.505 --> 00:31:15.773
Information Administration

00:31:16.574 --> 00:31:18.476
and Commerce
to work with the FCC

00:31:18.476 --> 00:31:22.580
to develop protections for
the radio frequency spectrum,

00:31:23.915 --> 00:31:26.317
facilitating commercial
space activities.

00:31:27.018 --> 00:31:28.486
And Recommendation Four directs

00:31:28.486 --> 00:31:30.288
the Executive Secretary
of the Council,

00:31:30.288 --> 00:31:32.357
in coordination with all
members of the Council,

00:31:33.057 --> 00:31:34.926
to develop recommendations
to streamline

00:31:34.926 --> 00:31:38.630
export control
regulatory requirements

00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:41.432
by 1st of January 2019,

00:31:41.432 --> 00:31:43.968
also as the Secretary described.

00:31:43.968 --> 00:31:49.440
If there are no objections
or questions,

00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:51.776
seeing none,
I would, as Chairman,

00:31:51.776 --> 00:31:53.177
direct the Executive Secretary

00:31:53.177 --> 00:31:56.314
to include these recommendations
in a decision memorandum

00:31:56.314 --> 00:31:57.915
for the President
of the United States.

00:31:59.684 --> 00:32:02.120
Secretary Ross
and Deputy Secretary Rosen,

00:32:03.054 --> 00:32:05.957
at our meeting later this year,
I'd also like you to support --

00:32:05.957 --> 00:32:08.259
or report to the Council
the details of the progress

00:32:08.259 --> 00:32:13.965
so that we are making against
the President's decision

00:32:13.965 --> 00:32:16.834
in completion of
the decision memorandum.

00:32:16.834 --> 00:32:19.470
Will you join me in thanking
