00:32:52.270 --> 00:32:56.774
I'd like to ask
Susan Gordon, who I have --

00:32:57.408 --> 00:33:00.778
and the President have come
to know and greatly respect.

00:33:00.778 --> 00:33:03.748
She is the Principle
Deputy Director

00:33:03.748 --> 00:33:05.917
for National Intelligence
for the United States.

00:33:05.917 --> 00:33:07.819
And Susan, maybe
you could give us

00:33:08.753 --> 00:33:11.622
a brief overview of
the security challenges

00:33:11.622 --> 00:33:13.424
that the United States faces

00:33:14.258 --> 00:33:15.493
in the space environment today.

00:33:16.828 --> 00:33:18.196
Deputy Director Gordon: Well,
thank you, Mr. Vice President.

00:33:18.796 --> 00:33:20.064
I'm delighted to be here today

00:33:20.064 --> 00:33:22.900
representing the women and men
of the intelligence community.

00:33:23.434 --> 00:33:27.105
You know, we are drivers,
and practitioners,

00:33:27.105 --> 00:33:29.741
and users of U.S. space.

00:33:30.641 --> 00:33:34.612
In fact, our history and space
history are inextricably bound.

00:33:35.146 --> 00:33:36.881
And we see the same excitement

00:33:36.881 --> 00:33:40.151
that you articulated in your
remarks about this moment.

00:33:40.785 --> 00:33:43.121
And they're resplendent
with opportunity even at --

00:33:43.121 --> 00:33:46.824
(audio break)

00:33:46.824 --> 00:33:47.925
-- Vice President.

00:33:47.925 --> 00:33:49.627
As your resident
intelligence officer,

00:33:49.627 --> 00:33:53.631
I often bring the sobering
information to any meeting.

00:33:53.631 --> 00:33:56.801
And so today what I thought
I'd do is to spend a few minutes

00:33:56.801 --> 00:33:58.069
and just describe the plans

00:33:58.069 --> 00:33:59.771
and actions of foreign
adversaries

00:33:59.771 --> 00:34:03.975
and competitors who would seek
to impede our operations

00:34:03.975 --> 00:34:05.743
or challenge our advantage.

00:34:06.511 --> 00:34:08.880
Russia and China are each
developing counter-space

00:34:08.880 --> 00:34:11.849
capabilities to use during 
a potential future conflict

00:34:11.849 --> 00:34:14.252
with the United States
to reduce U.S.

00:34:14.252 --> 00:34:16.754
and allied advantage
and effectiveness,

00:34:16.754 --> 00:34:19.223
eroding our
information advantage.

00:34:20.124 --> 00:34:22.427
Both countries
have robust jamming

00:34:22.427 --> 00:34:24.862
and cyber-attack
capabilities today

00:34:24.862 --> 00:34:27.131
and can threaten our satellite
ground infrastructure.

00:34:28.099 --> 00:34:31.035
Russian and China destructive
anti-satellite weapons,

00:34:31.035 --> 00:34:35.273
including missiles, lasers,
and orbital weapons,

00:34:35.273 --> 00:34:38.576
will probably reach initial
operation capability

00:34:38.576 --> 00:34:39.844
in the next few years.

00:34:40.878 --> 00:34:42.680
Russian lawmakers have promoted

00:34:42.680 --> 00:34:45.750
military pursuit
of anti-satellite missiles

00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:48.286
to strike low-earth-orbiting
satellites,

00:34:48.986 --> 00:34:50.655
and Russia is testing
such a weapon.

00:34:52.056 --> 00:34:54.425
Both Russia and China
are developing laser

00:34:54.425 --> 00:34:56.327
anti-satellite weapons to dazzle

00:34:56.327 --> 00:34:59.230
or damage sensitive
space-based optical sensors,

00:34:59.964 --> 00:35:03.000
and Russia and China continue
to conduct sophisticated

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:04.769
on-orbit activities,

00:35:04.769 --> 00:35:08.339
such as rendezvous
and proximity operations

00:35:08.339 --> 00:35:11.309
that are intended to advance
counter-space capabilities.

00:35:12.577 --> 00:35:14.512
Military reforms
in China and Russia

00:35:14.512 --> 00:35:17.815
over the past few years
indicate an increased focus

00:35:17.815 --> 00:35:21.352
on establishing
operational airspace forces

00:35:21.352 --> 00:35:24.889
and integrating attacks against
space systems and services

00:35:24.889 --> 00:35:27.325
with military operations
in other domains.

00:35:28.593 --> 00:35:30.294
China's People's Liberation Army

00:35:30.294 --> 00:35:33.197
has formed counter-space
military units

00:35:33.865 --> 00:35:37.435
and begun operational training
with counter-space systems,

00:35:37.435 --> 00:35:39.971
including the ground-launched
anti-satellite missile

00:35:39.971 --> 00:35:42.273
that was initially
tested in 2007.

00:35:44.108 --> 00:35:47.144
Now, the idea of space threats
also includes the use of space

00:35:47.144 --> 00:35:49.814
to enable or empower
military operations

00:35:51.415 --> 00:35:53.384
on the earth's surface.

00:35:53.384 --> 00:35:55.453
Foreign countries
will continue to improve

00:35:55.453 --> 00:35:58.656
their military and dual-use
reconnaissance, communications,

00:35:58.656 --> 00:36:00.558
and navigation systems,

00:36:00.558 --> 00:36:02.393
in terms of the numbers
of satellites,

00:36:02.393 --> 00:36:05.162
the breadth of their capability,
and the application for use.

00:36:06.163 --> 00:36:08.533
Another nation-state
and non-state actors

00:36:08.533 --> 00:36:12.169
will gain access to advanced
space-enabled technology

00:36:12.169 --> 00:36:16.073
in the coming years as the
global space industry expands.

00:36:17.141 --> 00:36:20.177
They will increasingly
have access to weather,

00:36:20.177 --> 00:36:23.047
communications, navigation,
and timing data for intelligence

00:36:23.047 --> 00:36:25.516
and military purposes.

00:36:25.516 --> 00:36:28.786
The panel will do a great job
of making my next point,

00:36:28.786 --> 00:36:32.456
but I'll briefly state that I'd
like to call the attention

00:36:32.456 --> 00:36:34.759
to China's impressive rise,

00:36:34.759 --> 00:36:36.594
and it is impressive
as a space power.

00:36:37.395 --> 00:36:40.231
They have increased the number
of their active satellites

00:36:40.231 --> 00:36:42.900
by more than an order
of magnitude since 2000,

00:36:43.668 --> 00:36:46.203
and a result of Beijing's
strong investment

00:36:46.203 --> 00:36:48.773
in its satellite and rocket
manufacturing capability.

00:36:49.974 --> 00:36:51.909
China's satellite technology

00:36:51.909 --> 00:36:53.844
has become increasingly
sophisticated,

00:36:54.378 --> 00:36:57.281
and a case in point is the
success that China has had --

00:36:57.281 --> 00:36:59.984
achieved in world-leading
ground-to-space

00:36:59.984 --> 00:37:01.919
quantum communications
experiments.

00:37:03.354 --> 00:37:07.625
I think, in sum, China has
the best politically supported

00:37:08.492 --> 00:37:10.828
and best resourced
foreign space program

00:37:11.562 --> 00:37:13.297
that we have seen
in many years.

00:37:13.898 --> 00:37:15.967
And its years
of intense activity

00:37:15.967 --> 00:37:17.168
are beginning to bear fruit.

00:37:18.369 --> 00:37:22.807
I think the panel is
perfectly placed to help us

00:37:22.807 --> 00:37:24.041
put all this in context.

00:37:24.041 --> 00:37:25.343
Thank you, Mr. Vice President.

00:37:25.343 --> 00:37:27.511
The Vice President:
Great, thank you, Susan.

00:37:27.511 --> 00:37:29.447
(Applause.)

00:37:29.447 --> 00:37:36.320
Very insightful. Sue's a great
American, and thank you.

00:37:36.320 --> 00:37:40.224
Thank you for that candid
and bracing overview.

